summary: For all the things Eve doesn’t tell her husband I do think she’s being honest here. It’s one of the few questions only someone...
caption:
For all the things Eve doesn’t tell her husband I do think she’s being honest here. It’s one of the few questions only someone like Niko can ask and the way it stills, freezes her and makes her at least consider? For just a moment?

Part of what makes this so good is that Eve’s own provocation plays a huge role in why things are the way they are; she’s a whirlwind of destruction herself. So when trouble gets her it gets the best of her. AND THAT HAS ME ECSTATIC. [via @thelma2017dirjoachimtrier​ — source]
